K so, I'm pissed at myself beyond comprehension, and the stupid thing is I knew not to get off but I did anyway.  I went to Janessa's house on Saturday, she owns the 2 horses I'm working with, Copper and Daisy.  I tacked up the 2 girls and  when I mounted neither would move worth a goddamn.  I started off on Daisy, she wouldn't move or bit rein no matter how hard I pulled on her mouth...so what did I do, you won't believe this I got off.  What an idiot, 3 years of her sitting and I get off and *teach* her its okay to ignore what I want and be lazy.  I then get on Copper, and she won't move worth anything either, I did get her moving a bit after persistance, I got a 15 metre straight line and then a 15 metre trot back, and she's supposed to be this excellent cutting horse that neck reins at the drop of a pin, that was a lie, she too wouldn't even bit rein.  But I did some ground work with her and got her responding, so I guess thats okay, but why for the love of god did I get off Daisy and heres the kicker.  I won't see her for a week!  Chances are she's going to be 6 thousand times worse and I'll be lucky if she even lets me get on.  Good job, splendid work.  Ruining horses.

Ya dumb fucker.
So today I got a job working with some nice lady's horses, Daisy and Copper.  They're so pretty haha
